<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>The User Management API provides endpoints for creating, reading, updating, and deleting user accounts. It supports authentication via JWT tokens and includes rate limiting for all endpoints.</p>

<h2>Authentication</h2>

<h3>JWT Token Authentication</h3>

<p>All API requests require a valid JWT token in the Authorization header.</p>

<ac:structured-macro ac:name="code">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="language">bash</ac:parameter>
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Authentication Header</ac:parameter>
  <ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[
curl -X GET "https://api.example.com/v1/users" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..." \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json"
]]></ac:plain-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>

<h3>Obtaining a Token</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Authenticate using <code>POST /auth/login</code></li>
  <li>Store the returned <code>access_token</code></li>
  <li>Include token in all subsequent requests</li>
  <li>Refresh token before expiration using <code>POST /auth/refresh</code></li>
</ol>

<ac:structured-macro ac:name="warning">
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p><strong>Security:</strong> Never expose tokens in client-side code, URLs, or logs.</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>

<h2>Endpoints</h2>

<h3>Users</h3>

<h4>List Users</h4>

<table>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Method</strong></td>
      <td><code>GET</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Endpoint</strong></td>
      <td><code>/users</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Description</strong></td>
      <td>Retrieves a paginated list of users</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Permissions</strong></td>
      <td><code>users:read</code></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Query Parameters:</strong></p>
<table>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th>Parameter</th>
      <th>Type</th>
      <th>Required</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>page</code></td>
      <td>integer</td>
      <td>No</td>
      <td>Page number (default: 1)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>limit</code></td>
      <td>integer</td>
      <td>No</td>
      <td>Items per page (default: 20, max: 100)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>status</code></td>
      <td>string</td>
      <td>No</td>
      <td>Filter by status: active, inactive, pending</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>search</code></td>
      <td>string</td>
      <td>No</td>
      <td>Search by name or email</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<ac:structured-macro ac:name="expand">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Example Request</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <ac:structured-macro ac:name="code">
      <ac:parameter ac:name="language">bash</ac:parameter>
      <ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[
curl -X GET "https://api.example.com/v1/users?page=1&limit=10&status=active" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN"
]]></ac:plain-text-body>
    </ac:structured-macro>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>

<ac:structured-macro ac:name="expand">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Example Response (200 OK)</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <ac:structured-macro ac:name="code">
      <ac:parameter ac:name="language">json</ac:parameter>
      <ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "usr_abc123",
      "email": "john.doe@example.com",
      "name": "John Doe",
      "status": "active",
      "role": "member",
      "created_at": "2024-01-10T08:00:00Z",
      "last_login": "2024-01-15T14:30:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "usr_def456",
      "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
      "name": "Jane Smith",
      "status": "active",
      "role": "admin",
      "created_at": "2024-01-05T10:00:00Z",
      "last_login": "2024-01-15T09:15:00Z"
    }
  ],
  "pagination": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 10,
    "total": 42,
    "total_pages": 5
  }
}
]]></ac:plain-text-body>
    </ac:structured-macro>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>

<h4>Get User</h4>

<table>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Method</strong></td>
